				<title>SCP-4273</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4273</link>
				<description>

&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;scp-image-block block-right&quot; style=&quot;width:300px;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/scp-4273/4273&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--resized-images/scp-4273/4273/medium.jpg&quot; style=&quot;width:300px;&quot; alt=&quot;4273&quot; class=&quot;image&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;scp-image-caption&quot; style=&quot;width:300px;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SCP-4273 prior to its initial exhibition of paranormal activity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Item #:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-4273&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Object Class:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;Euclid/Uncontained&lt;/span&gt; Neutralized&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special Containment Procedures:&lt;/strong&gt; No testing necessary, do not request access unless for the purpose of regularly scheduled inspections of formerly anomalous materials. In the event that future inspections re-confirm a lack of anomalous properties, SCP-4273 may be disposed of at the discretion of the acting Research lead, after submitting appropriate forms indicating the rationale and documentation of its inertia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-4273 was the Florentine diamond, a crown jewel belonging to the Habsburg family. It was possessed by an object-bound, non-corporeal, and intelligent entity self-identifying as Karl I, the last Emperor of the Austro-Hungarian Empire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When light was beamed through with an intensity of at least 400 lumens, and SCP-4273 was placed next to a flat surface with the undocumented “proper size &amp;amp; orientation”, a two-dimensional humanoid image resembling Emperor Karl would be projected onto that surface for as long as the light was being pointed at it through SCP-4273. Although unable to produce sound, SCP-4273 was able to hear and communicated with the help of lip-reading interpreters. It could not project force into the physical world but had awareness of its surroundings, whether or not any illumination was present.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although the original documents have been lost, secondary records of information provided by SCP-4273 indicates that it had knowledge which was verified by historical fact as could best be ascertained at the time. SCP-4273 claimed to have taken the Florentine diamond into exile, and bound his immortal being to its form in order to ensure he would always be available to reclaim the Austrian or Hungarian thrones.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After Emperor Karl’s physical form expired in 1922, SCP-4273 briefly continued its pursuit of restoration before turning its attention to undoing its current existence. It was at this point that SCP-4273 was first documented by paranormal researchers covertly being funded by the KPD (Communist Party of Germany). It is believed that their intent was to deliver SCP-4273 to Soviet authorities in Moscow in order to further historical research and possible propaganda value, however the conspicuous and highly valuable nature of SCP-4273 prevented this from being carried out before March 6, 1933, when the KPD was forcibly dissolved by the Nazis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The next record of SCP-4273 is in South America, in the possession of jewelers believed to be connected to the Marshall, Carter &amp;amp; Dark Auction House. Following its discovery, the body of Karl I was exhumed for observation by agents of the SCP Foundation. Autopsy showed that, although the dental records and other identifying marks were present, the body had only been deceased for six years instead of the twenty-four years which had passed since the Emperor’s death.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This discrepancy has not yet been explained, but as SCP-4273 has displayed no anomalous properties since rediscovery and as such it is considered Neutralized as of January 1st, 1954.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;scp-image-block block-right&quot; style=&quot;width:450px;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/scp-4273/karlfamily&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--resized-images/scp-4273/karlfamily/medium.jpg&quot; style=&quot;width:450px;&quot; alt=&quot;karlfamily&quot; class=&quot;image&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;scp-image-caption&quot; style=&quot;width:450px;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emperor Karl I, pictured with his family at his coronation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;by &lt;span class=&quot;printuser avatarhover&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pixelatedharmony&quot;  &gt;&lt;img class=&quot;small&quot; src=&quot;http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=7179583&amp;amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;amp;timestamp=1610251540&quot; alt=&quot;pixelatedharmony&quot; style=&quot;background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=7179583)&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pixelatedharmony&quot;  &gt;pixelatedharmony&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 09 Jan 2021 22:28:17 +0000</pubDate>
												<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <div style="text-align: right;"></div> <div class="scp-image-block block-right" style="width:300px;"><a href="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/scp-4273/4273"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--resized-images/scp-4273/4273/medium.jpg" style="width:300px;" alt="4273" class="image" /></a> <div class="scp-image-caption" style="width:300px;"> <p>SCP-4273 prior to its initial exhibition of paranormal activity.</p> </div> </div> <p><strong>Item #:</strong> SCP-4273</p> <p><strong>Object Class:</strong> <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Euclid/Uncontained</span> Neutralized</p> <p><strong>Special Containment Procedures:</strong> No testing necessary, do not request access unless for the purpose of regularly scheduled inspections of formerly anomalous materials. In the event that future inspections re-confirm a lack of anomalous properties, SCP-4273 may be disposed of at the discretion of the acting Research lead, after submitting appropriate forms indicating the rationale and documentation of its inertia.</p> <p><strong>Description:</strong> SCP-4273 was the Florentine diamond, a crown jewel belonging to the Habsburg family. It was possessed by an object-bound, non-corporeal, and intelligent entity self-identifying as Karl I, the last Emperor of the Austro-Hungarian Empire.</p> <p>When light was beamed through with an intensity of at least 400 lumens, and SCP-4273 was placed next to a flat surface with the undocumented “proper size &amp; orientation”, a two-dimensional humanoid image resembling Emperor Karl would be projected onto that surface for as long as the light was being pointed at it through SCP-4273. Although unable to produce sound, SCP-4273 was able to hear and communicated with the help of lip-reading interpreters. It could not project force into the physical world but had awareness of its surroundings, whether or not any illumination was present.</p> <p>Although the original documents have been lost, secondary records of information provided by SCP-4273 indicates that it had knowledge which was verified by historical fact as could best be ascertained at the time. SCP-4273 claimed to have taken the Florentine diamond into exile, and bound his immortal being to its form in order to ensure he would always be available to reclaim the Austrian or Hungarian thrones.</p> <p>After Emperor Karl’s physical form expired in 1922, SCP-4273 briefly continued its pursuit of restoration before turning its attention to undoing its current existence. It was at this point that SCP-4273 was first documented by paranormal researchers covertly being funded by the KPD (Communist Party of Germany). It is believed that their intent was to deliver SCP-4273 to Soviet authorities in Moscow in order to further historical research and possible propaganda value, however the conspicuous and highly valuable nature of SCP-4273 prevented this from being carried out before March 6, 1933, when the KPD was forcibly dissolved by the Nazis.</p> <p>The next record of SCP-4273 is in South America, in the possession of jewelers believed to be connected to the Marshall, Carter &amp; Dark Auction House. Following its discovery, the body of Karl I was exhumed for observation by agents of the SCP Foundation. Autopsy showed that, although the dental records and other identifying marks were present, the body had only been deceased for six years instead of the twenty-four years which had passed since the Emperor’s death.</p> <p>This discrepancy has not yet been explained, but as SCP-4273 has displayed no anomalous properties since rediscovery and as such it is considered Neutralized as of January 1st, 1954.<br /></p> <div style="text-align: center;"> <div class="scp-image-block block-right" style="width:450px;"><a href="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/scp-4273/karlfamily"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--resized-images/scp-4273/karlfamily/medium.jpg" style="width:450px;" alt="karlfamily" class="image" /></a> <div class="scp-image-caption" style="width:450px;"> <p>Emperor Karl I, pictured with his family at his coronation.</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pixelatedharmony" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=7179583&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251540" alt="pixelatedharmony" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=7179583)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pixelatedharmony" >pixelatedharmony</a></span></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
