						 <div style="text-align: right;"></div> <p><strong>Item #:</strong> SCP-5134</p> <p><strong>Object Class:</strong> Safe</p> <p><strong>Special Containment Procedures:</strong><br /> SCP-5134 is contained within a locked suitcase. The key to the suitcase is kept by the O5 council and may be given to personnel with level 4 clearance or higher. Only level 4 personnel or higher may access its containment chamber. In the middle of SCP-5134's containment chamber is a pedestal. The suitcase holding SCP-5134 is rested upon it.</p> <p><strong>Description:</strong><br /> SCP-5134 resembles a leatherbound book. Inside its pages are made of parchment. The book also appears to be strangely in perfect condition even though it has been estimated to be over one thousand years of age. When an individual reads the book the individual's name will appear on it in gold lettering</p> <div class="footer-wikiwalk-nav"> <div style="text-align: center;"> <p>&#171; <a class="newpage" href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-5133">SCP-5133</a> | SCP-5134| <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-5135">SCP-5135</a> &#187;</p> </div> </div> <p>by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/triangleclipse" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=7060229&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251540" alt="Triangleclipse" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=7060229)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/triangleclipse" >Triangleclipse</a></span></p> 
