					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-5127</guid>
				<title>SCP-5127</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-5127</link>
				<description>

&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;scp-image-block block-right&quot; style=&quot;width:300px;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcS9yH0JA5go418GMsLtQgpXMcgmieXmgGGuGA&amp;amp;usqp=CAU&quot; style=&quot;width:300px;&quot; alt=&quot;images?q=tbn:ANd9GcS9yH0JA5go418GMsLtQgpXMcgmieXmgGGuGA&amp;amp;usqp=CAU&quot; class=&quot;image&quot; /&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;scp-image-caption&quot; style=&quot;width:300px;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SCP-5127; &amp;quot;Rose-Coloured Glasses&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Item #:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-5127&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Object Class:&lt;/strong&gt; Safe&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special Containment Procedures:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;SCP-5127 is to be kept within a standard secure storage locker at Site-64. Access requires minimum Clearance 2 while being deemed in satisfactory psychological condition by site psychiatric staff. Supervising personnel are not to look through SCP-5127 unless the object is being worn. Personnel accessing SCP-5127 are required to submit to a psychological screening after each session.&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;em&gt;See Addendum 5127.2&lt;/em&gt;) SCP-5127 is to be kept within a darkened secure storage unit with controlled ventilation at Site-64. Access requires minimum Clearance 3 while being deemed in satisfactory psychological condition by site psychiatric staff. SCP-5127 is not to be exposed to any source of light, natural or otherwise, while outside of a testing environment. Exposing SCP-5127 to light for extended periods is forbidden, as instances of SCP-5127-1 have been shown to pose chemical and reality hazards. Areas exposed to SCP-5127-1 must be immediately ventilated with HEPA or equivalent HVAC filters to prevent Site exposure.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;While there is no inherent threat in not doing so,&lt;/span&gt; SCP-5127 is to be kept in a darkened containment unit during transport to prevent unintended use. SCP-5127 can be transported unescorted, provided appropriate measures are taken to prevent unauthorized usage or exposure to light.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;While SCP-5127 otherwise maintains pristine condition, it is to receive professional polishing once annually to prevent accidental wear on the lenses.&lt;/span&gt; SCP-5127 is not to be handled without proper personal protective equipment (PPE). Future requests for polishing are under review.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Temporary Containment Procedure Update:&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;em&gt;See Addendum 5127.1&lt;/em&gt;) Per Containment Committee Order 5127.S64.15.1, Dr P█████ is no longer permitted to interact directly with SCP-5127 outside of a testing environment. This order shall persist indefinitely, until such a time a consensus regarding Dr P█████&#039;s mental state has been reached.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-5127 is a material object resembling circular pink spectacles&lt;sup class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;footnoteref-789390-1&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot; class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;  &gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; with no immediate exceptional qualities. The location of origin remains unknown, but the time of creation has been dated to the 1840s by Site-91&#039;s anthropologists. When SCP-5127 is worn or otherwise looked through, all external stimulus is altered to cause feelings of happiness and joy (otherwise referred to as a &amp;quot;rosey retrospection&lt;sup class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;footnoteref-789390-2&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot; class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;  &gt;2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;quot;). Subjects are usually aware that the cause of this effect stems from SCP-5127, and SCP-5127 can be removed from the wearer at any time. Some subjects have reported that usage of SCP-5127 is comparable to a small dosage of Ecstasy (&lt;em&gt;3,4-Methyl​enedioxy​methamphetamine&lt;/em&gt;) differing only in that the effect ends immediately upon removal instead of the standard 3-6 hours. Results vary depending on the mental state and psychological triggers of the subject, but all subjects have reported a general feeling of serenity. SCP-5127&#039;s bliss-inducing properties can cause addiction in subjects subjected to long-term use.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SCP-5127-1 is the designation given to &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;light&lt;/span&gt;luminescent vapour translated and produced by SCP-5127. SCP-5127-1 is a pink chemical vapour consisting of dopamine, serotonin, and oxytocin in high concentrations. When the airborne chemicals present in SCP-5127-1 come into contact with a biological organism, the chemical is absorbed into the bloodstream via the nearest available entry method&lt;sup class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;footnoteref-789390-3&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot; class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;  &gt;3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;. Direct contact with SCP-5127-1 is comparable to consistent doses of MDMA&lt;sup class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;footnoteref-789390-4&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot; class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;  &gt;4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;. Long-term exposure is fatal and will cause death by chemical overdose.&lt;br /&gt;
The density, concentration, and composition of SCP-5127-1 are dependent on the type and brightness of light distributed through SCP-5127; with natural light causing little to no production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Discovery:&lt;/strong&gt; Purchased for £7 at ████ Antiques, an antique shop in Windsor, UK, by Foundation personnel. SCP-5127&#039;s anomalous attributes were discovered when a researcher from Site-91 &amp;quot;tried them on&amp;quot; before their subsequent purchase. SCP-5127 was later transferred to Site-64 after Site-91 ruled out any possible xenobiological or thaumaturgical origins.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experiment-5127-01:&lt;/strong&gt; Dr A███, in an attempt to test SCP-5127&#039;s effective range, propped the object into a position at which it could be viewed through, placed a portrait in front of SCP-5127, and proceeded to move backwards. Dr A███ concluded that SCP-5127&#039;s effective range was the human eye&#039;s ability to see through it. Stating that: &amp;quot;The painting just kept getting more and more beautiful.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experiment-5127-02:&lt;/strong&gt; A camera was placed behind one of SCP-5127&#039;s lenses. The footage was reported to have no anomalous properties other than being pink tinted. It seems that SCP-5127 is only effective when &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;used by humans&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;em&gt;See Experiment-5127-03; Experiment-5127-05&lt;/em&gt;) directly observed by creatures that can see.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experiment-5127-03:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-5127 was placed on various kinds of animals&lt;sup class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;footnoteref-789390-5&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot; class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;  &gt;5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; and the status of each specimen was documented. All instances in which the subject could see through SCP-5127 reported activation of their various pleasure centres, with increased serotonin and dopamine production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experiment-5127-04:&lt;/strong&gt; One (1) D-class diagnosed with chemically-imbalanced depression was instructed to wear SCP-5127 as one usually would. The D-class reported feeling &amp;quot;unbothered and carefree&amp;quot; and proceeded to sing a rendition of Louis Armstrong&#039;s &lt;em&gt;What A Wonderful World&lt;/em&gt;, despite there being no green trees or flowers of any kind in the vicinity. When the object had been removed from the D-class (only minimal resistance was present) the subject reported that he no longer suffered from depressive episodes, but was able to experience feelings related to sadness again.&lt;sup class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;footnoteref-789390-6&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot; class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;  &gt;6&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experiment-5127-05:&lt;/strong&gt; One (1) D-class was given a standard tactical flashlight (250 Lumens) and asked to shine light through SCP-5127 and observe the object&#039;s effects. Upon shining the beam through SCP-5127&#039;s left lens, the beam was amplified by approximately 2.5x in brightness, with a final result of light as bright as 630 Lumens. The &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;light&lt;/span&gt;luminescent vapour produced and emitted from SCP-5127, hereby designated SCP-5127-1, has properties similar to its source of origin. The only new property exhibited by SCP-5127-1 is that its optical manipulation is observable to all sighted parties. If a sufficiently bright light source is used to create SCP-5127-1, the light produced can engulf large areas. It is impossible to burn an individual or item using the object&#039;s natural magnification properties due to the moisture concentration of SCP-5127-1; no matter how strong the light source.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Addendum 5127.1:&lt;/strong&gt; Dr P█████ received SCP-5127 during its transit period from Site-91 to Site-64, where it had been previously monitored by Dr A███. For the duration of transit, and a significant measure of time while in Site-64&#039;s custody, Dr P█████ used SCP-5127 for his personal enjoyment and developed an addiction to SCP-5127&#039;s euphoric effects. Due to the lack of briefing on the effects of SCP-5127 other than: &amp;quot;(the object) is safe to wear&amp;quot;, administrative action has not been taken against Dr P█████. The only exception being the restriction of access to SCP-5127, which was submitted at Dr P█████&#039;s request.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The following interview was conducted by Site-64&#039;s psychology team after Dr P█████ was taken into custody, and SCP-5127 was placed back in containment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviewer:&lt;/strong&gt; Dr Andy Westenfelt, Site-64&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Interviewee:&lt;/strong&gt; Dr P█████, Site-64&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[BEGIN LOG]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Westenfelt:&lt;/strong&gt; How are you feeling today Doctor-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr P█████:&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;em&gt;In Mandarin Chinese&lt;/em&gt;) Cut the shit, Andy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Westenfelt:&lt;/strong&gt; I know I&#039;m the only other one in the room that can speak Mandarin, but they&#039;re going to translate it anyway so you might as well use English.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr P█████:&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;em&gt;In English&lt;/em&gt;) How the fuck do you think I feel? I&#039;m in withdrawal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Westenfelt:&lt;/strong&gt; Well, that&#039;s fair enough. Since you want to get right to it, why&#039;d you do it?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr P█████:&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;em&gt;Groans&lt;/em&gt;) Could I get some water, please?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(&lt;em&gt;Dr Westenfelt gestures, and a glass of water is brought to Dr P█████&lt;/em&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Westenfelt:&lt;/strong&gt; But why &lt;em&gt;did&lt;/em&gt; you do it █████?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr P█████:&lt;/strong&gt; Quite frankly I didn&#039;t expect the rollercoaster I got.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Westenfelt:&lt;/strong&gt; Rollercoaster?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr P█████:&lt;/strong&gt; Well yeah, A███ said that they were safe to wear. Guess he didn&#039;t have to wear them much when they were looking for (&lt;em&gt;A Brief Pause&lt;/em&gt;) magic?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Westenfelt:&lt;/strong&gt; Thaumatic signatures, yeah.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr P█████:&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;em&gt;Chuckles&lt;/em&gt;) Well that&#039;s Yorkshire for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(&lt;em&gt;Both doctors continue the friendly conversation for a while until Dr Westenfelt redirects back to the main topic&lt;/em&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Westenfelt:&lt;/strong&gt; So how was the experience?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr P█████:&lt;/strong&gt; Nice at first. Everybody wants to stress a little less, but it just got worse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Westenfelt:&lt;/strong&gt; Could you define &amp;quot;worse&amp;quot; for me?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr P█████:&lt;/strong&gt; Well, okay. So imagine being a tad bit drunk, but all the time. You are happy, warm, not a care in the world. Yet you &lt;em&gt;know&lt;/em&gt; that people are looking at you a little funny, but that doesn&#039;t make you want to stop, right? You consider it, so you take &#039;em off but the world is just so painstakingly dull. Before you know it they&#039;re right back on your face and you won&#039;t think about this again for a week. It was like that if that makes any sense.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Westenfelt:&lt;/strong&gt; Would you consider using (SCP-5127) again?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr P█████:&lt;/strong&gt; Well maybe. (&lt;em&gt;A Brief Pause&lt;/em&gt;) Actually no. Not unless I needed to. In fact, keep it away from me, okay? I know that withdrawal gets worse before it gets better and I don&#039;t want easy access to it in case I start slipping.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Westenfelt:&lt;/strong&gt; I&#039;ll see what I can do.&lt;br /&gt;
[END LOG]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr P█████ was afterwards demoted to E-class for initial quarantine and assessment. Dr P█████ has since been rehabilitated and has resumed his research at Site-64 after returning to C-class status. At his request, Containment Committee Order 5127.S64.15.1 remains in place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Addendum 5127.2:&lt;/strong&gt;After approximately 14 hours of accidental direct light exposure, the concentration of SCP-5127-1 in Site-64&#039;s anomalous object lockerroom was dense enough to incapacitate Dr Berg and two of his research personnel. This initiated a level 3 evacuation of Site-64&#039;s northern quadrant until sufficient ventilation could be provided. SCP-5127-1 was subsequently reclassified as a vapour, and containment protocol was updated accordingly. Dr Berg&#039;s consequent request to process SCP-5127 as a possible biochemical weapon has been denied.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Addendum 5127.3:&lt;/strong&gt; While being tested at Site-91, Dr A███ remarked on how SCP-5127&#039;s euphoria-inducing qualities could be implicated to assist any individuals infected with &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4042&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;SCP-4042&lt;/a&gt;. This request is pending approval, but the Foundation&#039;s consistent attempts to monitor and contain instances of &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4042&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;SCP-4042-2&lt;/a&gt; continue.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Scribe&#039;s note:&lt;/em&gt; This document was originally composed at Site-91 before being amended and completed by Site-64. SCP-5127 was originally contained and documented in the United Kingdom before being transferred to a facility in the United States. Therefore, it is composed in British-English to preserve its comprehensive integrity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;by &lt;span class=&quot;printuser avatarhover&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/izaacpowers&quot;  &gt;&lt;img class=&quot;small&quot; src=&quot;http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6533554&amp;amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;amp;timestamp=1610251540&quot; alt=&quot;IzaacPowers&quot; style=&quot;background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6533554)&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/izaacpowers&quot;  &gt;IzaacPowers&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;footnotes-footer&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Footnotes&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;footnote-footer&quot; id=&quot;footnote-789390-1&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;  &gt;1&lt;/a&gt;. Also known as &amp;quot;glasses&amp;quot;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;footnote-footer&quot; id=&quot;footnote-789390-2&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;  &gt;2&lt;/a&gt;. Referencing the idiom rose-coloured glasses: optimism, the tendency to see things in a positive light&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;footnote-footer&quot; id=&quot;footnote-789390-3&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;  &gt;3&lt;/a&gt;. Skin and bodily orifices are susceptible to SCP-5127-1. SCP-5127-1 has not shown an ability to penetrate artificial coverings.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;footnote-footer&quot; id=&quot;footnote-789390-4&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;  &gt;4&lt;/a&gt;. Street name: Ecstasy&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;footnote-footer&quot; id=&quot;footnote-789390-5&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;  &gt;5&lt;/a&gt;. A golden retriever, a siamese cat, a guinea pig, a sand puppy, and a star-nosed mole&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;footnote-footer&quot; id=&quot;footnote-789390-6&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;  &gt;6&lt;/a&gt;. Mental state of the subject was recorded over a period of three (3) weeks before scheduled termination&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</description>
