>Topic and Prompt of the month!</span></h1> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><span style="font-size:150%;"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Open&nbsp;FAQ</a></span></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><span style="font-size:150%;"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;FAQ</a></span></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p><br /></p> <div style="text-align: left;"> <h3><span>what's this?</span></h3> <p>Underread and Underrated is a project intended to shine a spotlight on, well, underread and underrated pages!</p> <h3><span>oh neat. What's the blurb for?</span></h3> <p>As part of the associated UaU initiative, each month we'll be picking an element of SCP lore that people outside the general gestalt might not know about. We're also hosting writing challenges involving said lore!</p> <h3><span>may i suggest [blank] for the topic?</span></h3> <p>Sure! Do note, however, that anything with a dedicated hub<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-654343-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" >1</a></sup> above +100 in rating can't be made topic. Sorry! D:</p> <p>Suggestions should be PM'd to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1613974&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251541" alt="UraniumEmpire" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1613974)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" >UraniumEmpire</a></span>!</p> <h3><span>oh cool how do i participate?</span></h3> <p>Just PM <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1613974&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251541" alt="UraniumEmpire" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1613974)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" >UraniumEmpire</a></span> a link to your piece and she'll post it on next month's &quot;Last Month's Pieces and Topic&quot; section!</p> <p>For artists: try to link to whatever social media page is hosting the art. It saves us space and ensures we have a solid reference.</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="content-panel centered"> <div class="panel-heading"> <p>Last Month's Pieces and Topic</p> </div> <div class="panel-body"> <h2><span><a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/fault-lines">Fault Lines</a> and the Gulf canon</span></h2> </div> <div class="panel-footer"> <p>The best of the past.</p> </div> </div> <div class="content-panel centered"> <div class="panel-heading"> <p>Topic + pick of this month!</p> </div> <div class="panel-body"> <h2><span><a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/new-age-hub">New Age</a></span></h2> </div> <div class="panel-footer"> <p>This month's piece.</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>New Age is a novel-length trilogy about the Chaos Insurgency. It's a bit of a long read, so let's not worry too much about the description, alright?</p> <h3><span>This month's challenge:</span></h3> <ul> <li><strong>For writers:</strong> &#8230; why don't you take a break for this one? It's a long read.</li> <li><strong>For artists:</strong> And if you feel inspired to draw a scene from it afterwards&#8230; well, the more the merrier!</li> </ul> <p>by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1613974&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251541" alt="UraniumEmpire" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1613974)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" >UraniumEmpire</a></span></p> <div class="footnotes-footer"> <div class="title">Footnotes</div> <div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-654343-1"><a href="javascript:;" >1</a>. Meaning a hub dedicated exclusively or primarily to the topic. GoI Formats would <em>not</em> count unless the primary content for the GoI is its formats.</div> </div> 
